{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aff6a1f9-bc9f-4e3f-9a49-e5818f8b4883","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — run tests with hot reload, re-running on file changes.\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only execute tests whose name contains that string.\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. Save a file and it will automatically re-run just that one test.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9d1eec7-ae6b-459d-9fcb-3a3f9ed29773","outputTokens":143},"id":"81b79b19-9a10-4aaa-b5b3-299d40514956","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:56:52.903Z","parentId":"d49f8ac4-2bdd-4aab-a1cc-10f2dcc2ad5b"}
